Note: This is a single-line comment at the start

Process called "main" takes argc as Integer, argv as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: This is a single-line comment inside a function

    Let x be 42 Note: This is an inline comment after code
    Let y be 100

    Note: These are three separate single-line comments
    Note: Each one ends at the newline
    Note: No :End Note, so each is independent

    Note: This one starts a multi-line block
    that spans multiple lines
    and provides detailed documentation
    about what this code does
    :End Note

    Note: This is single-line again
    Note: Because there's no :End Note attached to these

    Let result be x plus y Note: Another inline comment

    Note: This demonstrates the rule - :End Note only applies to the NEAREST Note: before it

    Note: Calculate and display the result
    print_integer(result)
    print_newline()

    Return 0
End Process
